Objective
To develop a Kafka consumer-producer application for the Cloudera_Exit project, capable of consuming messages in JSON format, parsing them with Avro, and producing them to another Kafka topic. This application should also support Kerberos authentication and have configurable logging and debugging options.

Overview
The application will:

Consume messages from a specified Kafka topic.
Parse the messages using Avro schemas.
Produce the parsed data to another Kafka topic.
Handle Kerberos authentication and secure communication.
Log application activities and write debug information based on configuration.
Data Flow
Kafka Consumer: Connects to the source Kafka topic and reads messages in JSON format.
JSON Avro Parser: Parses incoming JSON messages using Avro schemas.
Kafka Producer: Sends parsed messages to the destination Kafka topic.
Logging: Captures detailed logs of processing steps.
Debug Output: Writes consumed messages to output files if debugging is enabled.
Configurations
JAAS Configuration
Purpose: To authenticate Kafka clients using Kerberos.
File Location: /path/to/kafka_client_jaas.conf
plaintext
Copy code
KafkaClient {
   com.sun.security.auth.module.Krb5LoginModule required
   useKeyTab=true
   keyTab="/path/to/user.keytab"
   storeKey=true
   useTicketCache=false
   principal="user@REALM";
};
KRB5 File Configuration
Purpose: To configure Kerberos client settings.
File Location: /etc/krb5.conf
plaintext
Copy code
[libdefaults]
    default_realm = REALM
    dns_lookup_realm = false
    dns_lookup_kdc = true

[realms]
    REALM = {
        kdc = kdc.example.com
        admin_server = admin.example.com
    }
Trusted Source and Configuration
SSL/TLS Configuration: Enable SSL to secure Kafka communications.
File Location: /path/to/truststore.jks
Configuration Example:
properties
Copy code
security.protocol=SASL_SSL
sasl.mechanism=GSSAPI
ssl.truststore.location=/path/to/truststore.jks
ssl.truststore.password=truststore-password
Application Logs Storage Details
Log Framework: Log4j
Log Directory: /var/log/cloudera_exit
Log Rotation: Daily rotation with a retention period of 7 days.
Output File Write Details
Debugging Flag: Enable debug output by setting debug.enabled=true in the configuration file.
Output Directory: /path/to/debug/output
File Naming Convention: consumed_messages_yyyyMMdd.log
